NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Boater was a bit unlucky that I had more points than TJ. Give Bonnie an average hand of 16. You don't know that for sure, but on average that is a good guess. I passed 1NT, so I have no more than 7. As a guess, say I have 5. So N/S could easily have 21 or 22 points at best, leaving at least 18 or 19 for E/W. Therefore, at this vulnerability, double was ok. The main problem is Bonnie is behind Boater, so all finesses are likely to lose, and that is a big minus.|
